    A &= \{ 1,2,3,4 \} \newline
    B &= \{ w,x,y,z \} \newline
\end{aligned}    
\begin{aligned}
    f &= \{ (1,y), (2,w), (3,x), (4,z) \}
\end{aligned}   Solution  This is onto since every element in $B$ is mapped to. It is also one-to-one since every element in $A$ points to something different.

