if $f: A \mapsto B$ and $g: B \mapsto C$ are bijections, then $g \circ f$ is also a bijection.


Proof


(one-to-one)
 Supposed that $g \circ f(x_1) = g \circ f(x_2)$, for some $x_1, x_2 \in A$, or in another notation,




%Aligned
