Proposition


Given two functions $f: A \mapsto B$ and $g: B \mapsto A$ are inverses if and only is their compositions are identities.




 %Aligned
\begin{aligned}
    g \circ f &= i_A \newline
    f \circ g &= i_B \newline
\end{aligned}





